  "doc_id": "57366",
  "text": "Kleene [CITATION_1] defined a binary operator x * y in the context of finite automata, which denotes the iterate of x and y. Intuitively, the expression x * y can choose to execute either x, after which it evolves into x * y again, or y, after which it terminates. Kleene formulated some algebraic laws for this operator, notably (in our notation) x * y = x · x * y + y. Copi, Elgot and Wright [CITATION_2] proposed a simplification of Kleene's setting, e.g. they defined a unary version of the Kleene star in the presence of an empty word. The unary Kleene star has been studied extensively ever since.",
